The paper proposes a novel algorithm based on the Estimation of Distribution Algorithms (EDA) framework and using Distributional Adversarial Networks (DAN) to generate new offspring. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and neural networks in general, as well as the focus on optimization and multi-objective problems, suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a Competitive Swarm Optimizer (CSO), which falls under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with optimization problems in large decision spaces, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
